A motorist and his male passenger were shot dead in Umbilo on Thursday morning. The gunmen fired a hail of bullets at them in Sarnia Road. Rescue Care spokesperson, Garrith Jamieson, said the men were declared dead on the scene. “There was nothing that paramedics could do for them. Three lanes had to be closed to traffic while police carried out investigations into the shooting. Traffic was badly affected,” he said, Police are investigating the motive for the double killing.